-- Tax Rebate Scheme for China's Hainan Province Based on 11% Rate, CCTV Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-27T00:23:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-27/china-s-hainan-province-tax-rebate-scheme-is-based-on-11-rate-cctv-says.html
The tax rebate scheme for China’s
Hainan province was set based on a 11 percent rate, China
Central Television reported today, citing Zheng Jianxin, a tax
official at the Ministry of Finance.  Hainan’s tax rebate scheme will start from purchases of 800
yuan, CCTV reported, citing Zheng.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
